    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="592"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/871.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Smith</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 23.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 57, of the
                    20th ultimo, in regard to the blockade of Cape Haitien by the Haitian
                    Government.</p>
                <p>In reply the Department desires to say that as your doubts that the blockade was
                    effective appear to be well founded, your action in not recognizing the blockade
                    is approved.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. Osborne</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
